	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I actually had a dream about a NES game. Can't recall how old (young) I was at the time, it was like 1-3 years since I saw NES and its games for first time, I think.
<br />
<br />Me and my friends were big fans of the Blaster Master at the time. It actually was the japanese version, we called it Metafight (the only latin word at the title screen). We had just one copy of it, and the cart was glitchy multi-game cart, making the game almost unbeatable. Most of friends gave up after third level, having no idea where to go. Me with a friend managed to go few levels further. There was a glitched boss with almost infinite health (you had to shoot it for real long time to make counter overflow, as I understand it now). I think we barely got to final level, but haven't found the final boss, it was just once, and my friend gave up, because it was too difficult to get there (we even leave console on pause at night sometimes).
<br />
<br />So, everyone gave up, and I had no cart (don't remember what happened to it, I think it completely broke after all), and no console, but still was obessed with the game, thinking about it all the time, and wondering how it ends. One night I had a dream I still remember, where I finally beat the game, and see the final cut. It was something about Jason (me?) walking on clouds.
<br />
<br />Years after this I've got console and another cart with the game, still the japanese version, but not glitchy, and actually beat it. Barely can remember how this happened. Afterwards I'm sure I beat both japanese and american versions on emulators, maybe even few times, but don't really remember this either.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


