	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I frequently have dreams about variations of real NES games that do not exist. Like Zelda II with a different world map, or Zelda 1 with a completely different map.
<br />
<br />Some of the dreams are of games that are kinda similar to existing games. There is an RPG that I dream of that looks like a cross between Dragon Warrior and Ultima: Warriors of Destiny (horrible game BTW, try it on PC, much better).
<br />
<br />And then there's the bat-shit-insane Zeldroidvania game I keep dreaming about. Those dreams are what I am basing my current project on, but with some of the insanity removed <img src="./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" />
<br />
<br />The strange thing is, every time I have one of these dreams about a particular game the games are the same as the last time I dreamed of them. My dreams are kinda weird like that. Every time I revisit the same theme in one of my dreams the details are usually exactly the same as the last time I dreamed of them.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
